:12pt">ut demand may provide a be falsely low result compared to the possible success of schemes.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> It is important to educate people about benefits of public transport rather than just accepting the status quo (of it frequently being seen as unpopular, unreliable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and therefore suffering from an ‘inbuilt’ lack of demand)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">2. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">To what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (e.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision of public transport t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">o isolated communities?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rural Cumbria, provision for schoolchildren is felt to be good – mix of private taxi at public expense and school bus. There is no special provision for them for leisure and evening bus services are infrequent (where they h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">appen at all).</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> There is some provision for elderly/passengers with disabilities by way of low access buses. Ideally all buses should eventually be low access. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">3.How effectively do Community Transport services address the needs of passengers in isolated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> communities? How could Community Transport be improved?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Our local Voluntary Car Service in Above Derwent is popular and well used, but it could not operate without financial help from Cumbria County Council &amp; the WI. Publicity, subsidy from CCC and publ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">icity are all vital. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">To what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on taxis and other demand-responsive transport services? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If one starts from the position that it is important to maintain rural communities rather than </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">allow them to wither on the vine and let the countryside become the preserve of the second home owners and holiday makers; then local people should only be expected to rely on demand led service where there is absolutely no alternative.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> In rural areas, in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">habitants already get a poorer quality service for many facilities than in urban regions so public funding should be made available to provide public transport. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">What are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isolated commun</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ities? How can these services be made more affordable? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Privatisation has allowed bus companies to cherry pick the profitable routes.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Bus companies should only be able to provide complete services so there is cross subsidy built in to the system.  In addi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tion provision of mixed services should be considered (e.g. school buses being used by other passengers, school taxi’s being publicised and shared, post-buses etc)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>